{"lemma":"عَرَقُ","slug":"عَرَقُ","root":"ع.ر.ق","root_slug":"ع-ر-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ر-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":16},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n28768","n28769","n28770","n28772","n28773","n28778"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to strip of flesh, to nibble"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be emaciated"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to sweat, to perspire"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make sweat, to promote perspiration"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to water down, to dilute (a drink)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to grow roots; to take root"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be deeply rooted"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to vein, to marble"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَرِقَ (ʕariqa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sweat, perspiration"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"arrack (a clear raisin liquor that turns cloudy when water is added)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plant stem, leaf stem"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"blood vessel","examples":[{"text":"فإذا أَرَدتَ فتح عرق أو وداج فخذ المبضع بين إصبعك الإبهام والسبّابة كأخذك القلم للكتابة به وليكن نصابه في راحتك وتخرج من رأسه خارج طرفي إصبعك المذكورين قدر طول ظفر إبهامك وأقلّ من ذلك إلى قدر نصف ظفر إبهامك ثم أفتح العرق إلى فوق شقّا بليغا برفق وخفّة. وأمّا التوديج يالقضيب وهو معلوم فتركب فيه المبضع وتخرج من طرفه خارج من القضيب قدر طول ظفر إبهامك، ولا تعجل بالضرب بالمبضع حتّى تقف على العرق بعينه وخاصة الوداجين، ولا تودّج حتّى تستوثق من الدابّة بالشكل والزيار ليألُ يضطرب وتختنق الدابّة بالخناق خنقا شديدا ليدرّ العرق. فإنّ ذلك موضوع خبيث وإن جاوزت يدك ربّما أصاب المبضع عرق الماء وهو المريء الدابّة فقتله.","english":"If you want to open a vein or jugular, take the scalpel between your thumb and index finger, take it like you take the quill for writing with it, so that its grip is in your palm, and you turn away from its head outwith the two tips of your said fingers by a length of the nail of your thumb and less than that by a half of the nail of your thumb, then you open the vein upwards making a sufficient cut with gentleness and levity. And what concerns the cutting the jugular with the known rod, you mount the scalpel in it and you move away from the rod’s tip by the length of the nail of your thumb, but don’t hasten with hitting with the scalpel until you have discerned the vein by its eye, particularly the two jugulars, and don’t do a jugular cut until you have provided for the security of the beast by hopples and a twitch, so you do not agitate or suffocate the beast at its throat by excessive choking, so the vein flows with abundance. This part being particularly perilous, if your hand go to far then the scalpel could hit the water vein [or windpipe], that is the oesophaghus of the beast, and it would kill it."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hereditary disposition"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"race, stock, descent"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"erg"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Ge'ez ዐረቀ (ʿäräḳä, “to be naked, to be orphaned, to be childless, to be bereft”).\n\nCognate to Ge'ez ዐረቀ (ʿärräḳä, “to strip naked”).\n\nFrom the root ع ر ق (ʕ r q) in the sense of plants “perspiring” roots or roots being naked or stripped from earth when looked upon; or metathesis from the root ع ق ر (ʕ q r) related to عَقَار (ʕaqār, “real estate, ground, land”), compare against its Aramaic cognate עִיקָּרָא / ܥܶܩܳܪܳܐ (ʿiqqārā, ʿeqqārā, “root”) and Old South Arabian 𐩲𐩧𐩤 (ʿrq, “collarbone; lowlying land, plain, depression”)."},"ipa":["/ʕa.raq/","/ʕirq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28768","headword_ar":"عَرْقٌ","root":"Erq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuraAqN","text_ar":"عُرَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) [the latter also a pl.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bone of which the flesh has been taken:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bone of which the flesh has been eaten:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bone of which most of the flesh has been taken, some thin and savoury portions of flesh remaining upon it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the former signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bone upon which is flesh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one upon which is no flesh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whereof most of that which was upon it has been taken, some little remaining upon it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of flesh-meat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaroqapN","text_ar":"عَرْقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaroqN","text_ar":"عَرْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bone with its flesh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuraAqN","text_ar":"عُرَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bone of which the flesh has been eaten:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) thus they are correctly expl. accord. to Ez-Zejjájee; and the like is said by AZ respecting ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuraAqN","text_ar":"عُرَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) but accord. to A'Obeyd, this signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of flesh-meat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and IAmb says that this is the right explanation, because the Arabs say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akalotu AlEuraAqa","text_ar":"اَكَلْتُ العُرَاقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and they do not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akalotu AlEaZoma","text_ar":"اَكَلْتُ العَظْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Har p.26:) [or, app., the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flesh-meat"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a bone: and likewise the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of trees,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that are cropped"},{"kind":"text","text":"by camels: (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuraAmN","text_ar":"عُرَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":)] the pl. (of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaroqN","text_ar":"عَرْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, Mgh, O) is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuraAqN","text_ar":"عُرَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, O, K,) which is extr, (IAth, K,) a pl. of a measure of which, as that of a pl., there are few instances, (ISk, S, O,) [see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAHN","text_ar":"جَنَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraAqN","text_ar":"عِرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, (IAar, K,) which is more agreeable with analogy. (IAar, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A road which men travel"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though they pared it]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that it becomes plainly apparent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA:) an inf. n. used as a subst. [properly so termed]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraqN","text_ar":"عَرَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", near the end."}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","TA","Mgh","IAth","ISk","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n28769","headword_ar":"عِرْقٌ","root":"Erq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain appertenance"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a tree; (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"root"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof; or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is beneath the ground;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA;) or its"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"branching roots"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"collectively"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) pl. [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuruwqN","text_ar":"عُرُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraAqN","text_ar":"عِرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraAqN","text_ar":"اَعْرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-  It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa","text_ar":"لَيْسَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liEiroqK ZaAlimK Haq~N","text_ar":"لِعِرْقٍ ظَالِمٍ حَقٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, O, Msb,) i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"li*iY EiroqK","text_ar":"لِذِى عِرْقٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaAlimK","text_ar":"ظَالِمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, O, Msb,) meaning (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no right pertaining"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to him who plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sows,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in land which another has brought into cultivation"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after it has been waste,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrongfully, in order that he may have a claim to that land:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb:) the epithet being tropically applied to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiroq","text_ar":"عِرْق"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) as it properly applies to the owner thereof: (Mgh:) but some, in relating this trad., say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liEiroqi ZaAlimK","text_ar":"لِعِرْقِ ظَالِمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", making the former noun to be a prefix to the latter, governing it in the gen. case. (O.) ―         -b3-  The roots of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroTaY","text_ar":"اَرْطَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euruwqu AlA^aroTaY","text_ar":"عُرُوقُ الاَرْطَى"},{"kind":"text","text":") are long, red, penetrating into the moist earth, succulent, compact, and dripping with water: and to them, in"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2019},{"kind":"text","text":"a trad., certain camels are likened in respect of their redness and plumpness and the compactness of their flesh and fat. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEuruwqu","text_ar":"العُرُوقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain plant with which one dyes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEuruwqu AlS~uforu","text_ar":"العُرُوقُ الصُّفْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain plant used by the dyers, called in Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zarodaJuwbap","text_ar":"زَرْدَچُوبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zarodN Juwbo","text_ar":"زَرْدٌ چُوبْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K, TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yellow wood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alhurodu","text_ar":"الهُرْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaAmiyraAnu","text_ar":"المَامِيرَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaAmiyraAnu AlS~iyniY~u","text_ar":"المَامِيرَانُ الصِّينِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkurokumu AlS~agiyru","text_ar":"الكُرْكُمُ الصَّغِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) all which are nearly alike. (TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqolapu AlxaTaATiyfi","text_ar":"بَقْلَةُ الخَطَاطِيفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bql","text_ar":"بقل"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEuruwqu AlHumoru","text_ar":"العُرُوقُ الحُمْرُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Madder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfuw~apu","text_ar":"الفُوَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one dyes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEuruwqu AlbiyDu","text_ar":"العُرُوقُ البِيضُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain plant that fattens women; also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmusotaEojilapu","text_ar":"المُسْتَعْجِلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b7-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuruwqN","text_ar":"عُرُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"seems sometimes to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Straggling plants"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stalks, spreading like roots:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janobapN","text_ar":"جَنْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b8-  And it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sprouts from the roots"},{"kind":"text","text":"of trees: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EusoluwjN","text_ar":"عُسْلُوجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b9-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiroqN","text_ar":"عِرْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"root, origin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"source, of anything:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"basis"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof. (TA.) [And particularly The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"origin"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man, considered as the root from which he springs: hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiroqu","text_ar":"عِرْقُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~araY","text_ar":"الثَّرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to be applied by Imra-el-Keys to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Adam,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as the root, or source, of mankind; or to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ishmael,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as, accord. to some, the root, or source, of all the Arabs: (see “ Le Diwan d'Amro'lkais, ” p. 33 of the Ar. text, and p. 103 of the Notes:) and the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraAqN","text_ar":"اَعْرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ancestors"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man. (Har p. 634.) [And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A quality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposition, possessed by a parent"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by an ancestor"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by a collateral of such person,"},{"kind":"text","text":"considered as the source of that quality of a disposition in a descendant or in a collateral of a descendant: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a quality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposition, when transmitted; a strain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a radical, a hereditary, an inborn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a natural, disposition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a radical,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hereditary, share"},{"kind":"text","text":"in some quality or the like: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraAqN","text_ar":"اَعْرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tadaArakahu A^aEoraAqu xayorK","text_ar":"تَدَارَكَهُ اَعْرَاقُ خَيْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Good qualities"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispositions possessed by a parent"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by an ancestor"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by a collateral of such a person,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strains of a good kind, extended to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraAqu $ar~K","text_ar":"اَعْرَاقُ شَرٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawo'K","text_ar":"سَوْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil qualities"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispositions"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strains of an evil kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEiroqu","text_ar":"العِرْقُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"das~aAsN","text_ar":"دَسَّاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The natural disposition is wont to enter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., to be transmitted to succeeding generations]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ds","text_ar":"دس"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Erqt fiyhimo Eiroqa sawo'K","text_ar":"عرقت فِيهِمْ عِرْقَ سَوْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ear~aqato","text_ar":"عَرَّقَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or, accord. to more common usage,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraqato","text_ar":"اَعْرَقَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She implanted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"engendered, in them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among them, an evil strain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"radical"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hereditary disposition"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Drb","text_ar":"ضرب"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu EiroqN fiY Alkarami","text_ar":"لَهُ عِرْقٌ فِى الكَرَمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has a radical,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hereditary, share in generousness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobleness of origin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, O:) and in like manner one says of a person between whom and Adam is no living ancestor,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu EiroqN fiY Almawoti","text_ar":"لَهُ عِرْقٌ فِى المَوْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has a radical,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heriditary, share in death"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning that he will inevitably die. (O. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EariyqN","text_ar":"عَرِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b10-  [Hence, app.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A little,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"modicum,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small quantity"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"admixture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of something]. One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi EiroqN mino HumuwDapK","text_ar":"فِيهِ عِرْقٌ مِنْ حُمُوضَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muluwHapK","text_ar":"مُلُوحَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In it is a little,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a modicum, of acidity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of saltness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Al$~araAbi","text_ar":"فِى الشَّرَابِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiroqN mina AlmaA='i","text_ar":"عِرْقٌ مِنَ المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In the wine is a small quantity"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"admixture"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) ―         -b11-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain appertenance"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the body; (O, Msb, K, TA;) i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hollow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"canal"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is the blood;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a blood-vessel; a vein,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an artery:"},{"kind":"text","text":"also any"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"duct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"canal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in an animal body: and sometimes, though improperly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a nerve:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any one of the appertenances"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the body"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that resemble roots:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] pl. [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuruwqN","text_ar":"عُرُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraAqN","text_ar":"عِرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraAqN","text_ar":"اَعْرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, K.) [Hence it may be applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A spermatic duct:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence, app.,] it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayokumo","text_ar":"عَلَيْكُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlS~awomi faA_in~ahu maHosamapN liloEiroqi","text_ar":"بِالصَّوْمِ فَاـِنَّهُ مَحْسَمَةٌ لِلْعِرْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Keep ye to fasting, for it is"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cause,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"means, of stopping venereal intercourse:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an impediment to venery, and a cause of diminishing the seminal fluid, and of stopping venereal intercourse"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T * and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hsm","text_ar":"حسم"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euruwqu AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"عُرُوقُ الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pores through which exudes the moisture of the earth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b13-  And (i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Erwq AlArD","text_ar":"عروق الارض"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aHomapu AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"شَحْمَةُ الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the significations of which see in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$Hm","text_ar":"شحم"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiroqN","text_ar":"عِرْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"body."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) Thus in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laxabiyvu","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَخَبِيثُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEiroqi","text_ar":"العِرْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is corrupt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"impure, in respect of the body"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Milk."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqatuka daAy^imapu AlEiroqi","text_ar":"نَاقَتُكَ دَايِمَةُ العِرْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thy she-camel has a constant flow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundance, of milk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has constant milk."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraqN","text_ar":"عَرَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first quarter.] ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Numerous offspring:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"milk and offspring;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^akovara Eiroqa A_ibilika waganamika","text_ar":"مَا اَكْثَرَ عِرْقَ اـِبِلِكَ وَغَنَمِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How abundant are the milk and offspring of thy camels and thy sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [See, again,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraqN","text_ar":"عَرَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first quarter.]       -A3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Salt land that gives growth to nothing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-  And (K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tract, of land exuding water and producing salt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that gives growth to trees,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that gives growth to the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"species of tamarisk called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TarofaA='","text_ar":"طَرْفَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) a signification the contr. of that in the next preceding sentence. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mountain that is travelled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"traversed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mountain that is rugged, and extending upon the earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"debarring one by reason of its height,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and not to be ascended, because of its difficult nature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but not long."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A small mountain"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apart from others."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Thus it has two contr. significations. (K.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thin"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habol","text_ar":"حَبْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elongated and elevated tract"},{"kind":"text","text":"(not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jabal","text_ar":"جَبَل"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the CK)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sand extending along the ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an elevated place:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuruwqN","text_ar":"عُرُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraAqN","text_ar":"عِرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", latter half, in two places.       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiroqu maDan~apK","text_ar":"عِرْقُ مَضَنَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiloqu","text_ar":"عِلْقُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDan~apK","text_ar":"مَضَنَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the latter of which is that commonly known, TA) signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing of which one is tenacious;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing held in high estimation, of which one is tenacious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S and K and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dn","text_ar":"ضن"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and for which people vie in desire:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in that art.:) but [said to be] used only in a case of negation: one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA huwa EinodiY biEiroqi maDan~apK","text_ar":"مَا هُوَ عِنْدِى بِعِرْقِ مَضَنَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is not, in my estimation, a thing of any value,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","O","Msb","K","Mgh","IAar","AHn"]},{"entry_id":"n28770","headword_ar":"عَرَقٌ","root":"Erq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sweat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moisture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fluid, that exudes"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * O, * K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"of an animal; (K, TA;) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water of the skin, that runs from the roots of the hair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a gen. n.; having no pl.; (TA;) or no pl. of it has been heard: (Msb:) Lth says, I have not heard a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaraqu","text_ar":"العَرَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but if it be pluralized, it should be, accord. to analogy,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraAqN","text_ar":"اَعْرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, TA.) ―         -b2-  It is metaphorically used [in a similar sense] in relation to other things than animals. (K.) [Thus] it signifies The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exuded"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moisture"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a well: (K:) and in like manner of earth, or land, when the dew, or rain, has percolated in it ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nataHa fiyhaA","text_ar":"نَتَحَ فِيهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":") so that it has met the moisture thereof. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dibos","text_ar":"دِبْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honey"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of dates; (K;) because it flows, or exudes, from them. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Milk;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it flows in the ducts ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euruwq","text_ar":"عُرُوق"},{"kind":"text","text":") [thereof] until it comes at the last to the udder: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"milk at the time of bringing forth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^akovara Earaqa","text_ar":"مَا اَكْثَرَ عَرَقَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganamiki","text_ar":"غَنَمِكِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How abundant is the milk of thy sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats, at the time of their bringing forth!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, O.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiroqN","text_ar":"عِرْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", latter half.] ―         -b5-  And (K) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"offspring"},{"kind":"text","text":"of camels: (S, O, K:) so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^akovara Earaqa A_ibilihi","text_ar":"مَا اَكْثَرَ عَرَقَ اـِبِلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How numerous are the offspring of his camels!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.) [See, again,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiroqN","text_ar":"عِرْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", latter half.] ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Advantage, profit, utility,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"benefit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA; in [several of] the copies of the second of which,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aqoEu","text_ar":"النَّقْعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~afoEu","text_ar":"النَّفْعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a recompense,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reward:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA; in some copies of the former of which,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~uraAbu","text_ar":"التُّرَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~awaAbu","text_ar":"الثَّوَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a little thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) likened to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earaq","text_ar":"عَرَق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning “ sweat ”]. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earaqu AlxilaAli","text_ar":"عَرَقُ الخِلَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing that one gives,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yields, for friendship:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a reward for friendship."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) A poet says, namely El-Hárith Ibn-Zuheyr, describing a sword named"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~uwn","text_ar":"النُّون"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, TA,) belonging to Málik Ibn-Zuheyr, which Hamal Ibn-Bedr took from him on the day when he slew him, and which El-Hárith took from Hamal when he slew him, (TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wayuxobiruhumo makaAna Aln~uwni min~iY\n                      \n                     \n                        wamaA A^uEoTiytuhu Earaqa AlxilaAli"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And he shall tell them the place of En-Noon, from me, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was not given it as a reward for friendship"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning, that I took this sword by force. (O, TA. [In the S, the former hemistich of this verse is given differently, and, as is said in the TA, erroneously.]) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiytu mino fulaAnK","text_ar":"لَقِيتُ مِنْ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earaqa Alqirobapi","text_ar":"عَرَقَ القِرْبَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(which is a prov., TA) means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I experienced from such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as expl. by As, who says that he knew not the origin thereof, (S, O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficulty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distress,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as expl. by IDrd: (O:) and it is said that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earaq","text_ar":"عَرَق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or sweat] is of the man, not of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qirobap","text_ar":"قِرْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or water-skin]; and the origin of the saying is, that water-skins ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qirab","text_ar":"قِرَب"},{"kind":"text","text":") are [generally] carried only by female slaves that bear burdens, and by him who has no assistant; but sometimes a man of generous origin becomes poor, and in need of carrying them himself, and he sweats by reason of the trouble that comes upon him, and of shame; (S, O;) wherefore one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taja$~amotu laka Earaqa Alqirobapi","text_ar":"تَجَشَّمْتُ لَكَ عَرَقَ القِرْبَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j$m","text_ar":"جشم"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ja$imotu A_ilayoka Earaqa Alqirobapi","text_ar":"جَشِمْتُ اـِلَيْكَ عَرَقَ القِرْبَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[likewise expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j$m","text_ar":"جشم"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: accord. to Ks, the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2020},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suffered fatigue, and imposed upon myself difficulty, for thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in coming to thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that I have sweated like the sweating of the water-skin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to A'Obeyd,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have imposed upon myself, in coming to thee, what no one has attained, and what will not be;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrbp","text_ar":"قربة"},{"kind":"text","text":"does not sweat: (O:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earaqu Alqirobapi","text_ar":"عَرَقُ القِرْبَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a metonymical expression for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficulty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distress;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because, when the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrbp","text_ar":"قربة"},{"kind":"text","text":"sweats, its odour becomes foul: or because it has no sweat; therefore it is as though one imposed upon himself an impossible thing: or it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the benefit of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrbp","text_ar":"قربة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (which is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the flowing of its water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"TA;) as though one imposed upon himself such a task that he became in need of the water of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrbp","text_ar":"قربة"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. of journeying to it; or it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safiyfap","text_ar":"سَفِيفَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plaited suspensory"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which the carrier of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrbp","text_ar":"قربة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"puts over his chest"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when carrying the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrbp","text_ar":"قربة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on his back"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) accord. to IAar, it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the suspensory"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEolaAq","text_ar":"مِعْلَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by means of which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrbp","text_ar":"قربة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is carried;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaquhaA","text_ar":"عَلَقُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, TA;) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":"being substituted for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA: see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) but he says also that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earaqu Alqirobapi","text_ar":"عَرَقُ القِرْبَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one's sweating with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrbp","text_ar":"قربة"},{"kind":"text","text":"by reason of the difficulty, or trouble, of carrying it; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaquhaA","text_ar":"عَلَقُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", that by which it is tied, or bound, and then suspended: (L, TA:) the former is also said to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraAq","text_ar":"عِرَاق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrbp","text_ar":"قربة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is sewed around it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or it means that one has imposed upon himself"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficulty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trouble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fatigue, like that of the carrier of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrbp","text_ar":"قربة"},{"kind":"text","text":", who sweats beneath it by reason of its heaviness. (K.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraqN","text_ar":"عَرَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A heat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single run,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a run at once, to a goal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limit."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaraY Alfarasu EaraqFA","text_ar":"جَرَى الفَرَسُ عَرَقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earaqayoni","text_ar":"عَرَقَيْنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The horse ran a heat"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two heats."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A row of horses,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of birds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any things disposed in a row;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraqapN","text_ar":"عَرَقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) or this latter is the n. un. [app. signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of such as compose a row"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraAqN","text_ar":"اَعْرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraqaAtN","text_ar":"عَرَقَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) [See an ex. in a verse of Tufeyl cited in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sdr","text_ar":"صدر"},{"kind":"text","text":", conj. 5; also cited in the present art. in the S and O.] ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any row of bricks, crude"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"baked, in a wall:"},{"kind":"text","text":"one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaY AlbaAniY EaraqFA waEaraqayoni","text_ar":"بَنَى البَانِى عَرَقًا وَعَرَقَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEaraqatayoni","text_ar":"وَعَرَقَتَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraqapF","text_ar":"عَرَقَةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The builder built a row of bricks and two rows thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraAqN","text_ar":"اَعْرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Roads in mountains;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaroqapN","text_ar":"عَرْقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) with fet-h and then sukoon. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Foot-marks of camels following one another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) n. un. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraqapN","text_ar":"عَرَقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [See an ex. of the latter voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaraqN","text_ar":"طَرَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waqado nasajona biAlfalaApi EaraqaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And they had woven in the desert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waterless desert, foot-marks in their following one another"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A plait of palm-leaves"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) &c. (S, O)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zabiyl","text_ar":"زَبِيل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so in the S and O] or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zinobiyl","text_ar":"زِنْبِيل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so in the K, both meaning the same, i. e. a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"basket,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is made therewith:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zinobiyl","text_ar":"زِنْبِيل"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"itself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or hence (S, O) it signifies also (S, O, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zabiyl","text_ar":"زَبِيل"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mikotal","text_ar":"مِكْتَل"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zinobiyl","text_ar":"زِنْبِيل"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of large size, woven of palm-leaves,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"capable of containing fifteen times as much as the measure termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DAE","text_ar":"ضاع"},{"kind":"text","text":", as some say, (Mgh, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thirty times as much as that measure:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) also pronounced ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaroqN","text_ar":"عَرْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b6-  [And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A suspensory"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zabiyl","text_ar":"زَبِيل"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HatiY~N","text_ar":"حَتِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HtY","text_ar":"حتى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A similar meaning has been mentioned above, in this paragraph.)] ―         -b7-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraqapN","text_ar":"عَرَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Raisins."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K. [But this is said in the TA to be extr.: and I think it to have been probably taken from some copy of a lexicon in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zibayb","text_ar":"زِبَيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"has been erroneously written for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zibayl","text_ar":"زِبَيل"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","S","O","TA","L","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n28772","headword_ar":"عُرَقٌ","root":"Erq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuraqapN","text_ar":"عُرَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n28773","headword_ar":"عُرُقٌ","root":"Erq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraAqN","text_ar":"عِرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (Lth, AZ, S, &c.)       -A2-  It is also expl. by IAar as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"People of soundness in religion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n28778","headword_ar":"عَرْقٍ","root":"Erq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaroquwN","text_ar":"عَرْقُوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaroquwapN","text_ar":"عَرْقُوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which it is a coll. gen. n."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}